    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if we go with the plain weave, we're basically creating this really dense, impenetrable layer. i guess we're looking for something that ensures nothing can penetrate the surface or get through the gaps in the threads, even if they're tiny. how do we test if the weave is actually \"closed\" enough to prevent any unwanted intrusion through the fabric?",
